This is the model Rating=0+1Origin[Internal]+2Salary+3Origin[Internal]Salary+.

The relationship between {0, 1, 2, 3} and {0, 1, 2, 3} are as folllowed:

0 = 0+1/2*1

1 = 1/2*1

2 = 2+1/2*3

3 = 1/2*3

confint(ols5)
##                  2.5 %     97.5 %

## year          1.058285   1.401786
confint(ols6)

## horsepower   -0.1441223 -0.1191866

95% CIs for the coefficient of year in regression i) is [1.058285, 1.401786]

95% CIs for the coefficient of year in regression ii) is [0.5269917, 0.7875439]

The coefficient of year in simple regression i) is an increase due to year that averages over all other differences including horsepower while the coefficient of year in ii) estimates the average mpg increase per increase in year for a fixed level of horsepower. Thus, the 95% CIs for the two coefficients of year are different.

The final model is violentcrimes.perpop = 85.510pct.kids.nvrmarried - 22.686pct.kids2parents + 13.112race.pctblack + 27.754pct.house.vacant + 1999.426.

BIC is used to find the best model with relatively small number of variables.

VIF is used to check multicollinearity.
